To further access the performance of the integrated O-BP/FM/PSK device, we measured the incident-photon-to-current efficiency, IPCE (%), as a function of the wavelength in the three-electrode configuration against Pt-mesh as the counter electrode and Hg/HgO as the reference electrode in 0.1 M KOH (~pH 13.17) solution. The IPCE was calculated as follows (Eq. (1)):1IPCE(%)=1240×[Jp][Pλ]×λ×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
